   Ok, here we go with another TS. Whole reason for the READNFO is to   
   once again give a massive thanks to DiGiDEATH for doing a great      
   job at cleaning this one up. It's been filtered a whole lot but it   
   still has some issues: The odd distorted audio segment, where the    
   audio goes really fuzzy and buzzy, the odd hint of 3D, whacked       
   colours and the odd shaking of the background which appears to be    
   another 3D effect. Not at all the best TS in the world, but it is    
   one of the more watchable out. We took the source and dropped it in  
   for conversion, adding a few of our own filters and then running     
   our custom encode settings. Turned out pretty nice. The audio goes   
   in and out of sync a little, but it's by the smallest amount that    
   i haven't bothered fixing it, as it's too minor an issue and i've    
   been busy. So remember it's free and should shut the kids up at      
   least. As always - Enjoy! 
